If we use Font.FromLogFont() to create a font, then it will goes to an exception in .Net Core Windows Forms:
```System.ArgumentException: Object contains non-primitive or non-blittable data.  ```

I debugged .Net Core source code, and it seems like following code lead to this issue:
```GCHandle gch = GCHandle.Alloc (logFont, GCHandleType.Pinned);```

If I cannot use [MarshalAs(UnmanagedType.ByValTStr, SizeConst=32)] in my font struct how should I define my struct? Is this a bug?

